verses.rendering:
They sharpen their tongues like a serpent;
the venom of a viper is under their lips.
Selah.

Guard me, LORD, from the hands of the wicked;
protect me from the violent one
who plans to trip my steps.

The arrogant have hidden a trap for me and ropes;
they have spread a net beside the path;
they have set snares for me.
Selah.

Let burning coals rain down on them;
let them be thrown into fire,
into flooding pits from which they cannot rise.
